                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <p>
                              <objectType>Catacomb</objectType>, explored and published by Bartoccini.  
               Of the several hundred loculi, 53 preserved, in whole or in part, the inscriptions that had been roughly incised or painted on stucco over the sealing slabs. 
                Not seen. </p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>Roughly incised or painted on stucco over the sealing slabs. The texts are brief, and consist of the name of the deceased and simple variants of the formula 
                           <foreign xml:lang="la">bixit annos</foreign>...; or in some 
               cases (e.g. nos. 8, 15, 40, 50) the Punic equivalent "<foreign xml:lang="xpu">avo sanu</foreign>..." usually within a <rs type="decoration">tabella ansata</rs>; many are accompanied by the <rs type="decoration">Chi-rho monogram</rs>, 
               usually plain, exceptionally with α, ω.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
